cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper deals with the application of deep learning techniques to extract field boundaries from satellite images. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The use of a deep convolutional neural network (CNN) for this task also suggests that the paper could be classified under the machine learning (cs.LG) category. The paper also discusses the use of conditioned inference, which is a technique used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with the generalization of the model across different sensors and time periods, which could be classified under the graphics (cs.GR) category.
